HIS DAD WAS SURPRISED BY THAT AND HIS MOTHER TOLD HIM THAT THEY WERE NOT RICH, THEY WERE POOR.
HIS FATHER WORKS AS A LIBRARY KEEPER, DOING CLEANING ANS WAXING.
THE YOUNG CLARK WAS LIVING IN THE LIBRARY.
DURING DAY TIME, HE HAD TO KEEP QUIET.
BUT AFTER THE LIBRARY WAS CLOSED, THE LIBRARY BECAME HIS PLAYGOUND.
HE READ A LOT OF BOOK.
WHEN HE WAS CONFUSED ABOUT SOMETHING, HE WOULD JUST GO AND FIND THE ANSWERS IN THE BOOK.
LATER, HE BECAME A COLLEGE GRADUATE, WHICH IS THE FIRST ONE IN THEIR FAMILY.
THIS IS LUCKY FOR A FAMILY THAT NONE OF THE PARENTS ARE RICH OR EDUCATED.
HE EVEN BECAME A PROFESSOR AFTER COLLEGE.
AND ALL OF THIS CAN'T BE DONE IF HE WAS LIVING IN THE LIBRARY WHEN HE WAS YOUNG
